The &quot;if I had cable&quot; argument isn't a correct analogy, but it doesn't
matter.  If you have been a DirecTV custerom for a while, you can get a
free receiver installed.  Ignore the old unit that your brother gave you
as example of wasteful practices.

I have had two DirecTV DVRs installed for free in the last six months.  New
cable, new receivers, new mutli-switch.

If the wasting of the old unit bothers you, call back and complain.  Tell
them that you have your finger poised to order a new free unit on the
DirecTV.com web site, which would certinaly cost them more than sending a
new card to you for free.

